tyle=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">The country doctor had come to 221B Baker Street, the famous lodgings of Sherlock Holmes, with an eerie tale-the legend of the Hound of the Baskervilles, the devil-beast that haunted the lonely moors around the Baskervilles’ ancestral home. The tale warned the descendants of that ancient family never to venture out on the moor. But Sir Charles Baskerville was now dead—and the footprints of a giant hound have been found near his body. Would the new heir of the Baskervilles meet the same dreadful fate? Sherlock Holmes and his faithful friend, Dr. Watson, are faced with their most terrifying case in this wonderful classic of masterful detection and bone-chilling suspense.<br style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">&nbsp;<br style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\"><b style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Includes an Afterword by Anne Perry</b></p></section><div class=\"more-link-wrap opened\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; width: 600px; text-align: center; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; background: none repeat-x transparent; padding-top: 60px;\"><br><br></div></div></div><div id=\"mobile-also-in-series\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\"><a name=\"#alsoinseries\" id=\"alsoinseries\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-shadow: none; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; background: transparent; color: rgb(255, 102, 0); text-decoration: none;\"></a></div>',7,'bookActive','',0,0,'2001-10-01'),(78,'Hard Times',0,320,12,18,'media/epubs/50.epub','media/bookimages/50.jpg',10,'3 days,7 days,14 days,